Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.86,0:00:07.35,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,The first-class mage exam will now begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.40,0:00:09.79,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,You will be tested as parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.79,0:00:15.89,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,The 57 exam-takers will split into teams \Nof three for the first test.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.09,0:00:30.01,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,You're there like the wind
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.01,0:00:34.63,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Closing your eyes at sunset
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.63,0:00:40.28,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what's on your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.55,0:00:45.60,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(857,1)\blur0.25\fs35\fnGeorgia\fsp3.9\c&HFFFE65&\pos(328,254)\clip(109,253,547,294)\t(3943,4986,\clip(109,253,110,294))}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.00,0:00:48.98,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With your eyelids open
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.98,0:00:53.56,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes shone like glass
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.56,0:01:00.33,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,It faintly smelled like a sunny day
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.26,0:01:11.46,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Clear up the sky, let flowers bloom
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.46,0:01:15.66,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Bloom and blame it on the sunny sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.66,0:01:20.05,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the rain, when it stops
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.05,0:01:25.05,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Will make you shine in the sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.05,0:01:30.45,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Calm the stirring sounds in my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.45,0:01:34.49,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,We go like the sunny wind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.49,0:01:38.90,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Go on and fly over that cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.90,0:01:43.73,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Further and further away
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.00,0:01:50.00,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(402,269.5)}Episode 19: Well-Laid Plans
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.00,0:01:59.66,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,See? I knew you could do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.74,0:02:02.55,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.41,0:02:08.01,Flashback,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Lawine is rough, but she \Npulls me along with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.99,0:02:14.45,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Our first battle against a dragon is tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.96,0:02:17.32,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Are you scared, Eisen?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.72,0:02:18.89,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,You're shaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.71,0:02:20.91,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.91,0:02:22.92,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I see. In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.55,0:02:25.28,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what? You're scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.73,0:02:26.73,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.99,0:02:33.36,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I'm scared, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.43,0:02:36.01,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of conversation is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.59,0:02:41.54,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd copy other adventurers \Nand inspire you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.54,0:02:44.67,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. It doesn't seem to have worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.06,0:02:48.32,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,No. Thanks to you, I'm no longer tense.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.32,0:02:51.27,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel, just be yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.27,0:02:55.20,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure this sort of thing \Ndiffers from party to party.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.58,0:02:58.81,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.09,0:03:07.95,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. It really does differ \Nfrom party to party.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.20,0:03:18.47,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We finally caught a Stille.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.85,0:03:20.66,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Now we don't have to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.66,0:03:23.73,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so relaxed?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.12,0:03:27.00,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,The hard part's still to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.72,0:03:32.61,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,We have to keep our Stille \Nfrom being stolen by other parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.29,0:03:35.59,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to fight other mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.98,0:03:45.37,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's review what we learned \Nfrom observing the Stille.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.79,0:03:50.52,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,First, like Frieren said, those birds \Nfly faster than the speed of sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.53,0:03:58.58,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,We could never catch up to it at that speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.30,0:04:01.43,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, they're as tough as dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.43,0:04:05.99,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Common attack spells have no effect, \Nand they break free of most restraints.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.94,0:04:10.00,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, they're sensitive to mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.00,0:04:13.69,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Even when we suppress our mana to \Napproach one, it quickly flies away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.59,0:04:27.41,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,The biggest problem of all is because the \NStille themselves have practically no mana,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.41,0:04:29.77,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,we can't find them using mana detection.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.12,0:04:33.14,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that, we have \Nno idea where they are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.14,0:04:34.78,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know how many there are either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.22,0:04:39.91,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,The only ones we ever spotted were \Nthose three yesterday morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.23,0:04:44.29,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,They're probably being cautious because \Nthe test-takers are searching for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.29,0:04:47.63,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Worst case, they might \Nnever show themselves again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.93,0:04:52.69,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,And even if we do find one, \Nwe have no idea how to catch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.69,0:04:54.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.10,0:05:01.78,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Last night I experimented with a spell \Nthat might be useful for catching a Stille.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.78,0:05:04.08,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I remember you going out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.08,0:05:05.53,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of spell is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.53,0:05:07.55,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I already showed you, Kanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.30,0:05:11.55,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,A spell that captures a bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.35,0:05:17.62,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a folk spell developed by \Na tribe of hunters during an era
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.62,0:05:21.71,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,when mages and magic were far more common.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.13,0:05:25.54,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, you did use \Na spell to restrain that creature.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.84,0:05:28.77,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,But wasn't that a monster and not a bird?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.77,0:05:30.99,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's folk magic, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.99,0:05:34.89,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It appears it can be used to capture \Nanything that broadly resembles a bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.89,0:05:37.03,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a powerful binding spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.03,0:05:39.14,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I think it'll probably work on the Stille.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.43,0:05:42.06,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you say so earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.06,0:05:45.54,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,We could've caught one yesterday \Nif we'd used that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.86,0:05:47.90,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, we couldn't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.52,0:05:52.24,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That spell's range is 50 centimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.24,0:05:54.52,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You have to get that close to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.02,0:05:57.14,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Fifty centimeters?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.14,0:05:59.78,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,How close have we gotten so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.78,0:06:02.18,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Three meters was the closest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.18,0:06:07.30,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but they noticed us \Nby the time we got within 20 meters of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.30,0:06:10.38,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,So we're one step short \Nof meeting the requirements.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.38,0:06:12.64,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,That's one huge step.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.29,0:06:18.79,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Just to confirm, it's difficult for you two \Nto stop the Stille with your magic, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.79,0:06:21.45,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,It'd probably work if we could freeze one,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.45,0:06:25.03,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,but they're sensitive to mana, tough, \Nand resistant to freezing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.03,0:06:28.21,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,It'd probably escape before \Nwe could fix it in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.78,0:06:33.41,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I bet we could easily stop one with my magic \Nif we had access to a ton of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.15,0:06:39.15,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,But my magic only allows me to control water.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.15,0:06:42.16,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I can't create it out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.06,0:06:46.53,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,So I can't use it unless \Nthere's water present,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.53,0:06:49.06,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,and mana struggles to penetrate \Nlarge bodies of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.06,0:06:52.95,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I'd probably have to infuse it \Nwith my mana beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.95,0:06:58.09,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I can quickly take control of even large \Namounts of water if it's scattered, like rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.09,0:07:04.06,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,But if I infused water with mana, the mana-\Nsensitive Stille would definitely stay away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.40,0:07:06.85,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Stay away?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.58,0:07:10.05,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. They'd stay away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.88,0:07:14.34,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This plan might work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.68,0:07:37.04,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,It's not bad, but it's risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.04,0:07:39.85,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,We'd be picking a fight \Nwith all the other teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.40,0:07:43.73,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,But I doubt we'll catch one otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.56,0:07:48.60,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you scared, Lawine?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.17,0:07:54.91,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Ow, ow, ow! You're gonna rip them off!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.74,0:07:58.91,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.91,0:08:00.76,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.17,0:08:09.13,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs18\pos(320,245)\bord1\blur2\3a&HAA&}4th Party\N{\fs22}Land, Second-Class Mage
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.49,0:08:09.12,DefaultTop,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,For now, let's hide until the test is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.13,0:08:14.64,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs18\pos(320,245)\bord1\blur2\3a&HAA&}4th Party\N{\fs22}Übel, Third-Class Mage
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.40,0:08:11.76,DefaultTop,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,What? That's no fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.76,0:08:14.65,DefaultTop,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,We're mages. We should fight openly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.64,0:08:18.01,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs18\pos(320,245)\bord1\blur2\3a&HAA&}4th Party\N{\fs22}Fern, Third-Class Mage
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.89,0:08:18.00,DefaultTop,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,Mages also avoid unnecessary fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.87,0:08:25.13,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,But first, we should get water.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.80,0:08:29.37,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,I think there was a lake \Nin the middle of the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.46,0:08:36.63,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, I'm glad \Nwe caught a Stille so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.15,0:08:41.33,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,If we can remain hidden until sunset, \Nwe'll pass the first test.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.30,0:08:44.34,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.34,0:08:47.33,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it won't be that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.66,0:08:52.59,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,I thought this was a road, \Nbut it's actually a dry riverbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.14,0:08:55.98,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but I saw similar \Nterrain in a few other places.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.00,0:09:01.57,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't there a barrier around the testing area?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.88,0:09:04.43,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That's standard for tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.09,0:09:08.82,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,They're powerful physical barriers \Nthat keep out even specks of dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.09,0:09:11.81,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Do they block water, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.23,0:09:13.01,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.68,0:09:18.21,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by the dryness, \Nthe barrier was erected over a week ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.86,0:09:23.93,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Then most of the water will have collected \Nin the lake in the middle of the valley.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.49,0:09:27.18,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Since the test-takers are living creatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.18,0:09:29.83,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,we need some amount of water to stay active.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.17,0:09:35.03,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't guarantee test-takers \Nwould gather around the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.80,0:09:37.08,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.37,0:09:39.59,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We can carry water with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.94,0:09:43.84,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,But the Stille, which are \Nalso living creatures, cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.84,0:09:47.66,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,I see. And those who have realized that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.66,0:09:51.40,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,will be waiting around the lake, \Nthe largest body of water in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.86,0:09:56.83,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I've made my decision. \NWe'll give up on finding water.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.83,0:10:01.55,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be tough. I'm already parched.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.55,0:10:04.24,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure we can find a small pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.24,0:10:06.70,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Is that sanitary?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.70,0:10:08.54,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps if we boil it.
