Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.57,0:10:37.07,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs18\pos(320,245)\bord1\blur2\3a&HAA&}8th Party\N{\fs22}Ehre, Second-Class Mage
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.78,0:10:45.33,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs18\pos(320,245)\bord1\blur2\3a&HAA&}8th Party\N{\fs22}Wirbel, Second-Class Mage
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.80,0:10:45.32,DefaultTop,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,What a pain in the ass. \NI was shooting to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.18,0:10:48.20,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,You're quick enough to react to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.57,0:10:54.09,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Well, whatever. \NLeave the cage with the Stille.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.09,0:10:55.85,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,And if we refuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.17,0:10:58.33,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Then there's no need for words.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.74,0:11:10.35,DefaultItalics,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The lake is that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.04,0:11:36.46,Default,TEST-TAKER A,0000,0000,0000,,They froze the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.46,0:11:38.47,Default,BLEI,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.47,0:11:40.08,Default,EDEL,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.39,0:11:43.48,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,That's the mana of one of \Nthe 2nd party's members.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.94,0:11:45.49,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,What are they thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.06,0:11:48.99,Default,WIRBEL,0000,0000,0000,,Are they trying to antagonize \Nall the other parties?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.98,0:11:58.60,Default,EDEL,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.60,0:12:00.65,Default,EDEL,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and melt it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.99,0:12:04.88,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Denken, what should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.36,0:12:08.33,DefaultTop,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a waste of time and effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.37,0:12:10.37,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs18\pos(320,245)\bord1\blur2\3a&HAA&}13th Party\N{\fs22}Denken, Second-Class Mage
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.33,0:12:10.88,DefaultTop,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in melting it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.37,0:12:13.87,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs18\pos(320,245)\bord1\blur2\3a&HAA&}13th Party\N{\fs22}Richter, Second-Class Mage
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.35,0:12:17.39,DefaultTop,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,After that showy display of magic, \Nthe Stille won't come near this lake again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.87,0:12:17.38,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs18\pos(320,245)\bord1\blur2\3a&HAA&}13th Party\N{\fs22}Laufen, Third-Class Mage
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.60,0:12:20.77,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll steal our Stille from the 2nd party.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.12,0:12:26.86,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,If they went this wild, \Nthey must have a plan to catch one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.58,0:12:52.03,DefaultItalics,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.49,0:13:02.20,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,Let's scatter for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.77,0:13:10.47,Default,EDEL,0000,0000,0000,,We have to melt the frozen lake quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.78,0:13:12.47,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Those fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.81,0:13:20.46,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Using that much magic to melt the ice \Nwill make the lake truly useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.30,0:13:23.95,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The Stille won't come near here again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.25,0:13:25.08,Default,PARTY B,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.08,0:13:25.60,Default,MOB 2,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.60,0:13:26.39,Default,MOB 3,0000,0000,0000,,That way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.39,0:13:31.46,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Those who realized that are searching \Nfor other watering holes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.46,0:13:33.67,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,but their mana detection is inadequate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.67,0:13:36.85,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,They won't be able to handle airborne threats.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.85,0:13:37.96,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,They're inexperienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.25,0:13:41.17,Default,TEST-TAKER B,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently the 2nd party froze the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.17,0:13:43.25,Default,TEST-TAKER C,0000,0000,0000,,Are they trying to ruin the test?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.25,0:13:46.56,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Ruin it? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.56,0:13:50.72,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The 2nd party has a well-laid plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.72,0:13:54.22,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Until we unravel it, we won't get anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.73,0:14:21.07,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Monsters got them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.56,0:14:31.34,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,They're already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.52,0:14:34.92,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.92,0:14:38.02,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, let's at least take them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.61,0:14:41.36,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,You can see them, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.36,0:14:43.40,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,They're circling above.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.65,0:14:46.91,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Not just one or two of them either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.20,0:14:50.00,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,There's magic on those corpses.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.00,0:14:53.52,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,They'll detect you \Nif you try to take them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.81,0:14:59.15,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Geisel. That's how they lure \Nand hunt their next prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.51,0:15:04.53,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,This party fell for their trap \Nand got themselves killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.08,0:15:06.68,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange that they chose
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.68,0:15:10.11,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,to administer the test in an area \Ninhabited by monsters like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.11,0:15:13.26,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's like they think nothing \Nof the test-takers dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.60,0:15:17.34,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Laufen, this is your first time \Ntaking the first-class exam, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.34,0:15:19.35,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Their reasoning is incredibly simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.15,0:15:24.89,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who would die here is \Nunqualified to be a first-class mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.35,0:15:27.23,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,The Continental Magic Association
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.23,0:15:29.90,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,is very mindful of maintaining \Nthe quality of first-class mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.63,0:15:33.22,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,There are those who still dream
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.22,0:15:37.59,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,of the powerful and noble mages \Nwho fought the Demon King's forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.91,0:15:41.00,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Damn their outdated ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.00,0:15:42.91,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised, Denken.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.91,0:15:46.28,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you'd be on their side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.28,0:15:49.02,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The quality of a mage is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.56,0:15:54.63,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,First-class mages need only \Nbe symbols of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.63,0:15:57.93,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how powerful you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.93,0:16:01.66,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,unless you can control people's hearts, \Nyou're as good as powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.08,0:16:06.91,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen countless mages \Nfar more skilled than myself
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.91,0:16:09.94,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,fall from power and be persecuted.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.59,0:16:15.70,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Great power is feared, \Nand rule by fear doesn't last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.94,0:16:20.32,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, magic isn't a noble thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.32,0:16:24.58,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So someone as weak as you \Nis perfect for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.05,0:16:27.74,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Watch your tongue, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.74,0:16:31.26,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I could beat you with my eyes closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.36,0:17:06.67,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,We've had no luck detecting the 2nd party.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.20,0:17:09.83,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,They're concealing their mana and hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.38,0:17:15.50,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,This place, too. All the watering holes \Nwe've seen are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.49,0:17:21.26,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's faint, but there's mana in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.85,0:17:24.56,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't sense anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.53,0:17:26.52,Default,LAUREN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.79,0:17:30.39,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,No. Is it the 2nd party?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.73,0:17:34.23,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt even the person \Nwho cast it could detect it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.23,0:17:36.49,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,There's that little in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.49,0:17:39.02,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,But a Stille could sense it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.62,0:17:42.52,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,They won't come near this water again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.85,0:17:44.91,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,What's the point of doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.43,0:17:49.03,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. There's a watering hole somewhere \Nthat doesn't contain mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.97,0:17:53.65,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,And that's where the 2nd party will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.19,0:17:55.70,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,How will we find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.79,0:17:59.68,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to rest a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.68,0:18:01.05,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Denken.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.05,0:18:03.52,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The testing area is enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.52,0:18:07.81,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be impossible to find a mage \Nwho truly doesn't want to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.14,0:18:09.39,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.39,0:18:12.53,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,They'll show us where they are eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.86,0:18:18.58,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,I infused every lake and pond \NI could find with mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.15,0:18:22.82,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible there are bodies of water \Nwe don't know about, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.59,0:18:27.58,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Just limiting the watering holes \Nthe Stille can use is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.42,0:18:31.80,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait here for a Stille.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.21,0:18:45.09,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? It's possible to completely \Nsuppress your mana?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.38,0:18:47.12,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Not completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.12,0:18:51.09,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,When I move, I release a little mana. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.75,0:18:53.48,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,I can't sense it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.27,0:18:55.98,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,We'll stand watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.09,0:19:00.91,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hold us back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.91,0:19:02.28,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.74,0:19:05.88,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,If it'd just rain, \NI could be useful in a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.88,0:19:08.42,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,But the barrier would deflect all of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.75,0:20:16.70,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, did you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.59,0:20:20.69,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,It was worth picking a fight \Nwith the other parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.09,0:20:23.45,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Now we'll pass the first test.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.05,0:20:26.94,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.84,0:20:29.20,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Found them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.20,0:20:32.01,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,So they used magic after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.01,0:20:37.09,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Not even the most skilled mage \Ncan conceal that moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.72,0:20:40.97,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's detected us. \NWe should get away from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.72,0:20:50.25,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it's too late to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.00,0:20:52.15,Default,SCHARF,0000,0000,0000,,Jubelade.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.18,0:21:02.28,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,Doragate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.74,0:21:05.89,DefaultItalics,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's like a cannon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.54,0:21:10.02,DefaultItalics,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,She backed off again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.30,0:21:21.95,DefaultItalics,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,Her technique is refined \Nand shows no openings, but it's old.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.95,0:21:24.43,DefaultItalics,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,It's like fighting against my grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.88,0:21:27.72,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,Ordinary offensive magic and defensive magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.72,0:21:30.35,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,You only use basic spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.35,0:21:32.42,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you playing things close to the chest?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.73,0:21:36.94,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I was taught to only use \Nbasic spells in combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.94,0:21:39.82,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,That's your master's philosophy, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.82,0:21:44.56,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She said it's enough \Nto defeat mages of this era.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.07,0:21:46.10,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.31,0:21:59.78,DefaultItalics,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,Again. What is this feeling of wrongness?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.78,0:22:03.25,DefaultItalics,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,It's like I'm fighting an experienced mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.08,0:22:05.81,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.81,0:22:10.92,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,If you fought Wirbel with your technique, \Nyou'd be dead by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.92,0:22:12.85,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.85,0:22:16.22,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You're the strongest one here, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.88,0:22:30.27,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,Wirbel is the captain of the \NNorthern Magic Corps that fought
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.27,0:22:32.63,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,against the remnants \Nof the Demon King's forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.14,0:22:35.49,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,He has far more experience in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.19,0:22:39.04,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,His magic is devoid of character.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.04,0:22:41.50,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,It's underhanded, \Nfor the sole purpose of winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.00,0:22:47.10,Default,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,The girl fighting Wirbel now \Nwill probably be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.13,0:22:49.41,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.04,0:22:53.18,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm alright (I'll be alright)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.18,0:22:56.10,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I hear you (I care about you)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.10,0:23:01.68,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The wind teases this hair that's longer now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.68,0:23:04.12,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,There's meaning in everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.62,0:23:07.10,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the days that came to a halt
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.70,0:23:13.74,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I finally understand,\NI've caught up to you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.74,0:23:17.53,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,See, things that couldn't have been
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.53,0:23:20.43,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Seen if it weren't for these eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.43,0:23:25.10,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why? They begin to overflow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.10,0:23:31.33,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I won't ask to see you, so at least
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.33,0:23:37.12,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Let me remember the past, just for today
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.12,0:23:43.13,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if we were to meet again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.13,0:23:49.01,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,No more hesitations, I'd choose the present
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.07,0:23:53.03,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime, anywhere, yah (wherever you are)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.03,0:23:57.68,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime, anywhere (smile for me)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.68,0:24:00.66,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be there (close your eyes,\Nand I'll always be there)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.66,0:24:03.41,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if there are no absolutes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.41,0:24:06.48,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm always aware of your thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.48,0:24:12.51,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Those tears will be alright,\Ndawn will surely break
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.96,0:24:19.42,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm whispering our lullaby\Nfor you to come back home
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.23,0:24:22.73,Default,ÜBEL,0000,0000,0000,,What hells have you seen?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.85,0:24:22.73,DefaultOverlap,SCHARF,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take your head off.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.03,0:24:24.73,DefaultTop,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll crush her.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.73,0:24:24.10,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,He's strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.75,0:24:26.23,DefaultOverlap,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting. Try me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.10,0:24:26.23,Default,LAND,0000,0000,0000,,This is impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.72,0:24:26.23,DefaultTop,EHRE,0000,0000,0000,,What's this sound?
